  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Part-Time Student Care and Admin Support (3 to 4 weekdays)",
  "description": "<p>We are an <strong>education centre located at Ang Mo Kio Avenue 3</strong>, seeking <strong>dedicated and responsible individuals</strong> to join our team as <em>Part-Time Admin & Student Care Support Staff</em>.</p><p><strong>Commencement: Immediate (Compulsory Training required)</strong></p><p><strong>Working hours</strong>:</p><p><strong>Weekdays| Mon, 12 to 6.30pm, Wed 12pm to 6.30pm, Thurs, 12 to 6.30pm, Fri 12 to 6.30pm. </strong><br /><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Closed on public holidays</strong></p><p>Job Description</p><ul><li>Attend to <strong>walk-in, phone, and email enquiries</strong> from parents and students</li><li><strong>Promote centre programmes</strong> and provide course consultation to prospective parents</li><li><strong>Coordinate and facilitate classes</strong>, ensuring smooth daily operations</li><li>Handle <strong>student registration, attendance-taking, and classroom assignment</strong></li><li>Supervise <strong>homework and spelling</strong> for Primary 1 to 6 students</li><li><strong>Follow up on enquiries</strong> and assist with <strong>collection of school fees</strong></li><li><strong>Communicate with teachers, parents, and students</strong> regarding class schedules or changes</li><li>Assist in <strong>marketing activities</strong> — taking photos, creating simple visuals for advertising use</li><li>Maintain a <strong>clean and organised environment</strong> (light housekeeping duties)</li><li>Support the Centre Manager in <strong>ad-hoc administrative or operational tasks</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum <strong>Diploma</strong> in any discipline</li><li>At least <strong>1 year of relevant experience</strong> in education or customer service preferred (training will be provided)</li><li>Must be able to <strong>work the hours stated above</strong> and commit for <strong>at least one year</strong></li><li><strong>Bilingual in English and Chinese</strong> (to liaise with Mandarin-speaking parents)</li><li><strong>Proficient in Microsoft Office</strong> and comfortable with digital tools</li><li><strong>Responsible, committed, and a good team player</strong></li><li><strong>Loves working with children</strong> and comfortable supervising homework</li><li>Able to attend <strong>2 days of compulsory training in January 2026</strong></li></ul><p>Interested candidates are invited to apply online with a comprehensive resume. We are regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p><br /></p><p>Benefits:</p><ul><li>Positive working environment</li><li>Easily accessible via MRT and public buses</li><li>Opportunity to gain hands-on experience in both student care and education administration</li></ul><h3><strong>How to Apply</strong></h3><p>Interested candidates are invited to apply online with a <strong>comprehensive résumé</strong>, including:</p><ul><li>Educational background</li><li>Work experience</li><li>Availability period</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
